          "title": "SOLID COLOR INTRO WITH IMAGE",
          "text": "It is very easy to think of the Early Mediaeval period as being dark, stark, and grim. An environment where most people lived in dwellings that were a single chamber, with small, unglazed, shuttered windows and a hearthstone in the middle of the floor and the smoke rising to filter out beneath the thatched eaves, does not appeal to our love of creature comforts.",
